{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012kxapzXF7Xw1F22jty1UTk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The documentation doesn't mention GEPA, fitness evaluation, or Pareto front anywhere. The self-evolution design doc (`docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`) references a `population/` directory but doesn't describe fitness or Pareto front mechanics — these are new concepts introduced by the fitness.go implementation.\n\nThe new code adds:\n- `FitnessRecord` and `CandidateFitness` types (in fitness.go)\n- `RunScoreRecord` and `PopulationConfig` types (in types.go)\n- Functions: `EvaluateRun`, `RecordFitness`, `LoadFitness`, `AggregateFitness`, `Dominates`, `ComputeParetoFront`, `FitnessPath`\n\nThe self-evolution design doc's \"On-Disk Evolution State\" section already shows `population/` with `meta.jsonl` and `assignments.jsonl`, but doesn't mention the fitness subsystem. The fitness data lives at `.cloche/evolution/fitness/<workflow>.jsonl` which is a new path not documented.\n\nLet me update the self-evolution design doc to reflect the fitness evaluation system."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":494,"cache_read_input_tokens":32221,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":494},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"42f5ff71-4041-485c-a632-f525157093bd","uuid":"da3e0e9a-36e8-4d6a-b1f5-4b86e62e2ffe"}
