{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HxXTRqxwaoJbUExnFp1RNR","type":"tool_result","content":"   455→Evolution is enabled by default. Users can disable it per-project for static\n   456→workflows.\n   457→\n   458→## GEPA: Fitness Evaluation and Pareto Front\n   459→\n   460→The Guided Evolutionary Prompt Adaptation (GEPA) subsystem extends the evolution\n   461→pipeline with multi-objective fitness evaluation for population-based prompt\n   462→evolution. It lives in `internal/evolution/fitness.go`.\n   463→\n   464→### Fitness Records\n   465→\n   466→Each completed run is evaluated into a `FitnessRecord` containing:\n   467→- **RunID / WorkflowName / Candidate** — identifies the run and its candidate\n   468→  (e.g. a prompt version)\n   469→- **Success** — whether the run reached `succeeded` state\n   470→- **RetryCount** — number of step re-executions (detected by counting duplicate\n   471→  step names in execution history)\n   472→- **Duration** — wall-clock time from start to completion\n   473→\n   474→Records are persisted as JSONL at `.cloche/evolution/fitness/<workflow>.jsonl`.\n   475→\n   476→### Aggregation\n   477→\n   478→`AggregateFitness` groups records by candidate and computes two objectives:\n   479→\n   480→1. **Success rate** — fraction of runs that succeeded\n   481→2. **Efficiency** — `1 / (1 + avgRetries + avgDurationMinutes)`, rewarding\n   482→   faster candidates with fewer retries\n   483→\n   484→### Pareto Front\n   485→\n   486→`ComputeParetoFront` returns the non-dominated set using standard Pareto\n   487→dominance: candidate A dominates B when A is at least as good in all objectives\n   488→and strictly better in at least one. The front represents the optimal tradeoff\n   489→between reliability and speed — no candidate on the front can be improved in one\n   490→objective without sacrificing the other.\n   491→\n   492→### Population Configuration\n   493→\n   494→Population-based evolution is controlled by `PopulationConfig`:\n   495→\n   496→```go\n   497→type PopulationConfig struct {\n   498→    Enabled          bool\n   499→    MaxCandidates    int\n   500→    MinRunsToPromote int\n   501→}\n   502→```\n   503→\n   504→## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n   505→\n   506→- **Step removal/mutation** — modifying or removing existing step definitions\n   507→  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n   508→- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** — automated revert from snapshots\n   509→- **Helpfulness tracking** — automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n   510→  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n   511→- **Cross-project learning** — sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n   512→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"42f5ff71-4041-485c-a632-f525157093bd","uuid":"a113ad41-e366-4121-8b75-a86c6a6a4040","timestamp":"2026-03-17T15:07:16.283Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md","content":"Evolution is enabled by default. Users can disable it per-project for static\nworkflows.\n\n## GEPA: Fitness Evaluation and Pareto Front\n\nThe Guided Evolutionary Prompt Adaptation (GEPA) subsystem extends the evolution\npipeline with multi-objective fitness evaluation for population-based prompt\nevolution. It lives in `internal/evolution/fitness.go`.\n\n### Fitness Records\n\nEach completed run is evaluated into a `FitnessRecord` containing:\n- **RunID / WorkflowName / Candidate** — identifies the run and its candidate\n  (e.g. a prompt version)\n- **Success** — whether the run reached `succeeded` state\n- **RetryCount** — number of step re-executions (detected by counting duplicate\n  step names in execution history)\n- **Duration** — wall-clock time from start to completion\n\nRecords are persisted as JSONL at `.cloche/evolution/fitness/<workflow>.jsonl`.\n\n### Aggregation\n\n`AggregateFitness` groups records by candidate and computes two objectives:\n\n1. **Success rate** — fraction of runs that succeeded\n2. **Efficiency** — `1 / (1 + avgRetries + avgDurationMinutes)`, rewarding\n   faster candidates with fewer retries\n\n### Pareto Front\n\n`ComputeParetoFront` returns the non-dominated set using standard Pareto\ndominance: candidate A dominates B when A is at least as good in all objectives\nand strictly better in at least one. The front represents the optimal tradeoff\nbetween reliability and speed — no candidate on the front can be improved in one\nobjective without sacrificing the other.\n\n### Population Configuration\n\nPopulation-based evolution is controlled by `PopulationConfig`:\n\n```go\ntype PopulationConfig struct {\n    Enabled          bool\n    MaxCandidates    int\n    MinRunsToPromote int\n}\n```\n\n## Future Work (Out of Scope)\n\n- **Step removal/mutation** — modifying or removing existing step definitions\n  (higher risk, needs careful design around backwards compatibility)\n- **`cloche evolve --revert <evo-id>`** — automated revert from snapshots\n- **Helpfulness tracking** — automatically detecting whether applied lessons\n  actually reduced failure rates, and pruning unhelpful ones\n- **Cross-project learning** — sharing knowledge base insights across projects\n","numLines":58,"startLine":455,"totalLines":512}}}
